<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-155-194  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 155 194.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  March 13 1989 v10 n11 p30(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Software AG enters into data center management; with 4GL tool athand. (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mahnke, John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Software AG of North America Inc introduces the Natural Operationsfourth-generation-language (4GL)-based data-center schedulingsystem for the centralized control of distributed, heterogeneouscomputing environments.andP;  The software, according to Software AG,is the only 4GL-based scheduling system on the market designed toautomatically manage and control all data center on-line and batchproduction, job flow, and resources.andP;  Natural Operations works bytreating an operating system as though it were a database.andO;Software AG has big hopes for Natural Operations, citing thatabout 75 percent of all data processing shops have not implementeddata-center scheduling programs.andP;  Natural Operations is easy toextend and the software can be customized to individualrequirements and applications.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Software AG of North America Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Natural Operations (Computer program) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Software PackagesProduct IntroductionManagement of EDPApplicationsAutomationFourth-Generation Languages.andO;Feature:   illustrationportrait.andO;Caption:   Roel Pieper. (portrait)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>